The paper focuses on developing an efficient gaze-based text input method for disabled people using eye movement. This involves the use of computer vision techniques such as gaze estimation and Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also involves image processing and computer vision techniques such as CNNs, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves natural language processing techniques such as the T9 input method, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper involves the creation of a large-scale dataset, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
